+## OpenAI Codex with a ChatGPT plan
+
+Use OpenAI Codex models through a ChatGPT Plus/Pro subscription without API
+keys or `config.toml` edits.
+
+Sign in once:
+
+```bash
+grok openai login
+# Headless / remote:
+grok openai login --device-code
+```
+
+The browser flow uses OpenAI's PKCE authorization flow and a fixed callback at
+`http://localhost:1455/auth/callback`. The device-code flow prints a URL and
+code. Credentials are stored separately from the xAI session in
+`~/.grok/openai_auth.json`, refreshed automatically, and sent only to the
+ChatGPT Codex backend.
+
+After login, the `openai-codex/*` models appear in the Ctrl+M picker. Switch
+inside the app with a pi-style provider/model reference and optional thinking
+level:
+
+```
+/model openai-codex/gpt-5.5:xhigh
+```
+
+The equivalent CLI form is:
+
+```bash
+grok -m openai-codex/gpt-5.5:xhigh -p "hello"
+```
+
+Use `grok openai status` to inspect the credential and `grok openai logout` to
+remove it. OpenAI login does not replace or modify the normal `grok login`
+session.
+
+---
+
